com.javadude.annotation
Annotation Type Property

public @interface Property

Defines a property for a JavaBean.

          The name of the property.

Element Detail

name

public abstract java.lang.String name
The name of the property. This will be used as the basis for the generated field name, and accessor methods.

plural

public abstract java.lang.String plural
The plural name of the property. This is only used for properties that have kind set to LIST, MAP, SET, UNMODIFIABLE_LIST, UNMODIFIABLE_MAP or UNMODIFIABLE_SET. If the plural name has not been set and the kind is one of these, plural will default to the value of name suffixed with an 's'.

Returns:
Default:
""

type

public abstract java.lang.Class<?> type
The type of the property. This type is used as the property type for simple properties, the element type for list/set properties, and the value type for map properties. Exactly one of type or typeString must be specified.

Default:
java.lang.Void.class

typeString

public abstract java.lang.String typeString
The type of the property. If the type is in the same package as the annotated bean, you don't need to package-qualify it. Otherwise, prepend with the package name. This type is used as the property type for simple properties, element type for list/set properties, and the value type for map properties. Exactly one of type or typeString must be specified.

Default:
""

keyType

public abstract java.lang.Class<?> keyType
The type of keys for map properties. This attribute is ignored for non-map properties. Exactly one of keyType or keyTypeString must be specified.

Default:
java.lang.Void.class

keyTypeString

public abstract java.lang.String keyTypeString
The type of keys for map properties. This attribute is ignored for non-map properties. If the type is in the same package as the annotated bean, you don't need to package-qualify it. Otherwise, prepend with the package name. Exactly one of keyType or keyTypeString must be specified.

Default:
""

reader

public abstract Access reader
The access level of the generated reader methods. If set to Access.NONE, the property will not be readable.

Default:
com.javadude.annotation.Access.NOT_SPECIFIED

writer

public abstract Access writer
The access level of the generated writer methods. If set to Access.NONE, the property will not be writeable.

Default:
com.javadude.annotation.Access.NOT_SPECIFIED

bound

public abstract boolean bound
Set to true if the property should be bound. Bound properties will fire events to registered PropertyChangeListeners. If at least one property in a Bean is marked as bound, the generated superclass will contain add/remove methods for PropertyChangeListeners as well as firePropertyChange methods.

Default:
false

kind

public abstract PropertyKind kind
The general kind of the property. This can have the following values:
  • PropertyKind.SIMPLE: A standard, single-value JavaBean property
  • PropertyKind.LIST: A multi-valued JavaBean property, represented as a java.util.List
  • PropertyKind.MAP: A multi-valued JavaBean property, represented as a java.util.Map
  • PropertyKind.SET: A multi-valued JavaBean property, represented as a java.util.Set
  • PropertyKind.UNMODIFIABLE_LIST: A LIST property, but the generated reader that returns the entire list will wrap it in Collections.unmodifiableList
  • PropertyKind.UNMODIFIABLE_MAP: A MAP property, but the generated reader that returns the entire list will wrap it in Collections.unmodifiableMap
  • PropertyKind.UNMODIFIABLE_SET: A SET property, but the generated reader that returns the entire list will wrap it in Collections.unmodifiableMap

Default:
com.javadude.annotation.PropertyKind.SIMPLE

omitFromToString

public abstract boolean omitFromToString
If true, this property will not be included in the generated toString() method. This is useful to avoid cyclic toString() definitions.

Default:
false
